# Pin POSIX-only files to LF regardless of the developer's `core.autocrlf`
# setting. The repo is consumed from Windows (PowerShell), macOS, and
# Linux containers (Docker builds). Without this, a Windows checkout
# converts shell-script line endings to CRLF, and the resulting `\r`
# in the shebang line breaks parsing inside alpine:
#   /bin/sh^M: bad interpreter: No such file or directory
# Manifested originally as apps/studio/docker-entrypoint.sh exiting 126
# inside the elfanaa_studio container on EasyPanel deploys committed
# from Windows.
*.sh           text eol=lf
Dockerfile     text eol=lf
*.dockerfile   text eol=lf
